    "en": {
      "title": "A surplus after 20 years of foreign trade",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "After 20 years, merchandise trade has created a surplus. In the month of June 2021, Sri Lanka's merchandise exports have become 1248 million US dollars and merchandise imports have become 1226 million US dollars.",
        "Thus, a trade surplus of 21 million US dollars has been created. The last time Sri Lanka had a merchandise trade surplus was in August 2002. That figure was 110 million US dollars.",
        "The decrease in the import of merchandise is mainly due to the significant decrease in the import of household appliances, sugar, steel, communication devices, machinery etc.",
        "In June 2021, the trade account deficit stood at US$ 652 million. However, the receipt of foreign labor remittances continues to show a further decline. Foreign labor remittances, which were US$ 478 million in June 2021, have decreased by 42.7 percent to US$ 274 million in June 2022."
      ],
